Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.23,0:00:16.24,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mizusawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.66,0:00:20.24,DCMain,MIZUSAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Umeki-san? Did you get \Nin touch with the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.43,0:00:23.86,Umeki,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(215,420)}Umeki Hiromichi (45)\NKanoya Construction Company President
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.51,0:00:23.87,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Sorry. My signal's weak, \Nso I couldn't reach them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.06,0:00:27.45,Mizugawa,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(214,382)}Mizusawa Sho (25)\NNonogaki Real Estate Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.31,0:00:26.30,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Could you try yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.30,0:00:27.65,DCMain,MIZUSAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.86,0:00:31.68,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful. It's slippery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.68,0:00:33.07,DCMain,MIZUSAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Aye-aye, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.68,0:00:39.51,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,The worst drought in 50 years, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.91,0:00:57.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right now at this moment, \Nlight pierces the darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:00:59.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Overcome all limits with \Nyour cool reasoning skills!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.02,0:01:00.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A skeleton is discovered \Nat the bottom of a dam!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.95,0:01:02.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A drama spanning time and space begins!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.82,0:01:04.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.46,0:01:06.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.21,0:01:08.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.02,0:02:56.01,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,1)}The Cursed Tears of Borgia (Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.75,0:02:54.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Cursed Tears of Borgia, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.84,0:03:02.53,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the case of \Nthe Cursed Tears of Borgia?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.81,0:03:07.12,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Forty years ago, while Beika \NCity-based Yamato TV was
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.31,0:03:10.61,Old Yamato TV,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(167,295)}Old Yamato TV\N(Approx. 1975)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.12,0:03:11.04,DCItalic,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}filming a show to commemorate \Ntheir fifth anniversary,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.04,0:03:17.06,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,the leading lady went missing \Nwhile wearing a prop ring set
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.06,0:03:21.05,DCItalic,,0000,0000,0000,,with the jewel known as the Tears of Borgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.20,0:03:28.30,Suspect is,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Suspect is Asahina Nagisa's assistant Saeki Yuri (30)?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.20,0:03:28.30,Newspaper Right Side,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,"Ran Off With\N the Tears of Borgia?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.20,0:03:28.30,Newspaper Left Side,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Shock Leaves \NAsahina Nagisa \NBedridden
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.66,0:03:28.31,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,However, suspect Saeki Yuri-san has \Nbeen discovered after 40 years
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.38,0:03:33.38,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,as a skeleton at the \Nbottom of a dried up dam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.27,0:03:37.32,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,"I Killed Them."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:38.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.10,0:03:42.42,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It was the title of the \Ndrama they were filming
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.21,0:03:42.60,Sumire,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(217,378)}Saeki Sumire (20)\NSaeki Yuri's Granddaughter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.42,0:03:47.03,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}when my grandmother allegedly ran off \Nwith the ring that was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.89,0:03:49.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.37,0:03:53.84,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, my grandmother \Nwas living here in Beika City,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.84,0:03:57.29,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,but after the case, the family fled
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:04:01.47,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,under cover of night because of the \Nabuse they suffered from the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.89,0:04:09.89,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,But the ring wasn't in the car \Nmy grandmother was found in!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:11.48,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, she...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.80,0:04:15.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Died after being stabbed in the \Nstomach with a fruit knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.15,0:04:17.09,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.09,0:04:20.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't mention that on the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.04,0:04:20.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.38,0:04:25.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa, the man who found the \Nbody, is one of my drinking buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.71,0:04:29.53,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,My grandmother is a victim!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.53,0:04:32.75,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Someone must've stolen the \Nring from her and killed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.27,0:04:38.99,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, it's a 40-year-old case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.45,0:04:41.56,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it will be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.14,0:04:45.26,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,But if you could at least \Nclear my grandmother's name...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.96,0:04:49.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.16,0:04:55.88,Mori Detective Agency,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.59,0:04:52.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.12,0:04:55.89,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.89,0:04:57.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:05:00.18,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.70,0:05:01.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.31,0:05:05.44,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,What did the police say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.44,0:05:09.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Like you said, it's a 40-year-old case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.66,0:05:13.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but during \Nthat time, it was underwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.19,0:05:15.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's very little evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.30,0:05:22.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,As it stands, they're unable \Nto conclude that your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.58,0:05:25.80,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,grandmother Saeki Yuri-san was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.80,0:05:28.18,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,B-But the knife...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.44,0:05:34.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That knife undoubtedly took \NSaeki Yuri-san's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:38.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But it's possible that, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:41.94,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,she regretted running off with \Nthe ring and committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.21,0:05:43.19,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.54,0:05:44.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a damn shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:54.67,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry we couldn't help, Sumire-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.67,0:05:58.74,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. I understand what Mori-san said.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.74,0:06:02.24,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,But when I think of how disappointed \Nmy mother will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.20,0:06:04.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sumire-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.68,0:06:11.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why was your grandmother suspected \Nof running off with the ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.22,0:06:13.34,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.34,0:06:18.30,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,It was my grandmother's job to \Ntransport the ring from the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.30,0:06:22.09,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Yamato TV studio in Beika City to \Nthe dam where they were filming.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.53,0:06:27.03,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,She went missing after she left the studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.32,0:06:30.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yamato TV was inside the aerial lighthouse
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.66,0:06:34.13,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,building that's being \Ndemolished right now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.13,0:06:35.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we head there now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:40.04,Safety First,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Safety First
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:40.04,Beika Tower Building,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Beika Tower Building\NRedevelopment Construction
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.01,0:06:46.85,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,There's no trace of it left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.85,0:06:48.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.33,0:06:51.55,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,My mother would be sad if she found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.69,0:06:54.44,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:06:56.17,DCMain,FEDORA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.17,0:06:56.81,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.17,0:07:01.57,DCMain,FEDORA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. You looked \Nlike an old acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.57,0:07:06.04,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,By Yuri-chan, did you mean Saeki Yuri?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.04,0:07:06.69,DCMain,FEDORA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.07,0:07:10.07,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Saeki Yuri was my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.38,0:07:13.06,Kanoya,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(216,1)}Kanoya Tatsuma (72)\NKanoya Construction Advisor
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.33,0:07:16.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.83,0:07:21.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we ran into an \Nacquaintance of your grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.32,0:07:22.35,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.35,0:07:25.66,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan's—rather,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.66,0:07:31.19,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,your grandmother's body was \Ndiscovered by my nephew Umeki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.71,0:07:34.22,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it might be fate,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.22,0:07:38.73,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,so I came to see the Yamato \NTV building being demolished.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.73,0:07:40.51,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know my grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.51,0:07:44.23,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,I actually used to work for Yamato TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.03,0:07:46.33,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.33,0:07:49.94,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan was a great assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.94,0:07:51.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.92,0:07:56.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the drama \N"I Killed Them"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.83,0:08:00.55,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.55,0:08:05.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't Sumire-san want to know \Nif her grandmother was innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.61,0:08:07.16,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.22,0:08:16.30,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. None of the staff \Nbelieved that Yuri-chan took the ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:17.10,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:20.84,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,I was part of the main staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.84,0:08:22.60,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it was so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:28.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? It was broadcast live?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.06,0:08:32.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,How can a drama be broadcast live?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.90,0:08:36.90,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, small stations like Yamato TV
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.90,0:08:40.62,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,didn't know much about video recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:44.86,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,So they turned that lack \Nof knowledge on its head
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.86,0:08:50.25,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,by calling "Killed 'Em" a "five \Nyear anniversary special live drama."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.25,0:08:52.20,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Killed 'Em?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.20,0:08:54.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That must be short for "I Killed Them."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:08:58.00,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,You figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.00,0:09:01.77,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,This industry has a habit \Nof abbreviating everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.64,0:09:05.59,Yamato TV,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Yamato TV
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.60,0:09:06.43,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,This is how we shot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.43,0:09:09.06,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one behind the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.06,0:09:10.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's so young.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.08,0:09:13.80,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,That's her! That's my grandmother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.80,0:09:16.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She looks just like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.51,0:09:24.23,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan and Asahina \NNagisa-chan were like sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.23,0:09:29.58,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,How long did the actress Asahina \NNagisa-san appear on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.58,0:09:32.80,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,She disappeared right after "Killed 'Em."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.81,0:09:37.55,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,She only debuted because she \Nwas a sponsor's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.07,0:09:43.93,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagisa-chan wasn't a bad girl,\Nbut she had terrible stage fright.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.95,0:09:48.68,I Killed Them,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,I Killed Them
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.55,0:09:48.69,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,I... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.69,0:09:53.37,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I killed them. I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.88,0:09:52.31,Nagisa,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(208,386)}Asahina Nagisa (22)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.37,0:09:55.24,DCItalic,YURI,0000,0000,0000,,Here, Nagisa-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.51,0:09:59.19,Yuri,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(211,1)}Saeki Yuri (30)\NNagisa's Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.42,0:10:00.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What about apples?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.95,0:10:05.84,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,She always had her peel \Nthem to help her calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.84,0:10:08.75,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Short strokes meant she was still anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.75,0:10:12.21,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Long strokes meant she'd \Nmanaged to calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.62,0:10:15.71,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,My grandmother was a good assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.19,0:10:21.22,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,But on that day, she traveled \Nseparately from Nagisa-chan
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.84,0:10:24.60,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,because she had to transport the ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.14,0:10:27.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.00,0:10:32.28,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Because there were rumors the \NAsahina family had purchased
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.28,0:10:35.08,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,counterfeit Tears of Borgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.49,0:10:46.39,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,The Asahina family requested that Western \Nhistory Professor Senju proclaim it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.39,0:10:48.75,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,was genuine before the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.41,0:10:55.00,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,The jewel had to be left at the studio \Nto accommodate the professor's schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.53,0:11:00.62,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan would bring it to the filming \Nlocation once he gave his testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.62,0:11:03.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,They could've rescheduled filming.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.93,0:11:06.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They can't do that, Ran-neechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:08.80,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, because it was broadcast live.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.71,0:11:14.98,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,I was at the filming location as a cameraman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.00,0:11:17.18,Yamato TV Camera,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Yamato TV
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.88,0:11:18.49,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagisa-chan was the only actress there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.22,0:11:25.49,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,As long as the Tears of Borgia arrived by \N20:20, it would be in time for the broadcast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.79,0:11:27.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been an important prop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.20,0:11:34.63,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,It was. It needed to arrive in time \Nfor its close-up during the climax.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.65,0:11:43.50,Yamato TV Camera,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26}Yamato TV
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.69,0:11:39.25,Kanoya Flashback,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(214,386)}Kanoya Tatsuma (32)\NCameraman
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.75,0:11:42.26,DCItalic,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Switching from studio to filming \Nlocation in three, two, one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.64,0:11:59.70,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,We did it with one camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.09,0:12:02.86,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,It was a chance to show off my skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.53,0:12:06.91,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,until she started slowly peeling apples.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.29,0:12:10.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She peeled apples in the drama?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:15.53,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It was Yuri-chan's \Nidea to help her calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.14,0:12:19.03,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Being an assistant sounds like hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.03,0:12:23.34,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Some actors even had her make cheat sheets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.34,0:12:25.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,For their lines? Why would they...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:28.68,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, because it was live.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.75,0:12:36.31,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't have time to rehearse, so \Nmemorizing lines was quite the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.31,0:12:40.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But ultimately, the ring \Nnever arrived, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.79,0:12:47.06,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case, we brought \Nthe prop ring with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.06,0:12:48.45,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a cheap one, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.45,0:12:49.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.25,0:12:52.45,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,But my grandmother went missing ever since...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.87,0:12:57.14,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,We were so distracted by the \Ncommotion after filming
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.14,0:13:01.35,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,that we put off worrying about Yuri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.35,0:13:02.46,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.88,0:13:04.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.63,0:13:07.85,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagisa-chan collapsed right when we finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.85,0:13:09.22,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.67,0:13:13.23,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,She actually had a 40 degree Celsius fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.23,0:13:15.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? She filmed in that condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.65,0:13:19.73,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,You can't cancel a live \Nbroadcast for an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.04,0:13:23.09,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,She knew that when she was cast.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.09,0:13:25.74,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't uncommon back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.74,0:13:29.76,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Does Nagisa-san still live in Beika City?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.76,0:13:33.62,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,In a nursing facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.34,0:13:36.61,DCMain,TATSUMA,0000,0000,0000,,It's called "Grand Light."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.10,0:13:39.63,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.98,0:13:42.46,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,Asahina-san is out right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.86,0:13:46.83,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't been told when she'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:48.86,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.64,0:13:51.29,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, front desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.73,0:13:53.64,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,What? You got separated?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.11,0:13:56.39,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's here to see her right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.63,0:13:59.17,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.80,0:14:08.77,Asahina,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Asahina
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.20,0:14:10.50,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,You looked away for a minute, \Nand she disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.57,0:14:15.52,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,You've already told her doctor, right? I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.69,0:14:26.33,DCMain,DOCTOR,0000,0000,0000,,She sometimes becomes panicked \Nbecause of an old trauma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.33,0:14:27.73,DCMain,DOCTOR,0000,0000,0000,,You have to be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.16,0:14:32.05,DCMain,DOCTOR,0000,0000,0000,,She mixes up her memories \Nof the present and the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.70,0:14:34.56,DCMain,DOCTOR,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I'm glad they found her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.56,0:14:36.31,Room 312,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Room 312
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.56,0:14:36.31,Asahina Room Plate,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Asahina
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.10,0:15:01.99,Nagisa Title,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(215,423)}Asahina Nagisa (62)\NFormer Actress
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.36,0:15:08.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.17,0:15:13.05,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun's over there. \NHe's on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.74,0:15:15.50,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Say, "ah."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.50,0:15:16.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:20.77,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's peel some more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.48,0:15:25.84,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,Asahina-san, you have guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.33,0:15:28.24,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Two young ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.37,0:15:34.77,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.96,0:15:47.36,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan, I'm sorry! Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.01,0:15:50.00,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.41,0:16:00.06,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan, I'm sorry! Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.06,0:16:01.64,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.64,0:16:03.15,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.27,0:16:13.06,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,She was supposed to be \Nfriends with my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.06,0:16:15.78,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did she scream like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:21.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Something happened between the \Ntwo of them that traumatized her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.92,0:16:27.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably what \NShinichi-niichan would say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.19,0:16:29.43,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,If only he were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.43,0:16:33.43,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He might know where the Tears of Borgia went.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.73,0:16:40.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sumire-san, do you know what \N"I Killed Them" was about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.06,0:16:44.40,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. There was once an old family that kept
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.40,0:16:48.25,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,the historically significant Tears of Borgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.96,0:16:54.94,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, there was a notorious \Nthief known as "Red Hood."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.48,0:17:00.80,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Red Hood declared that he would \Nsteal the Tears of Borgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.93,0:17:04.54,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,The police were powerless against him,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.14,0:17:10.08,Red Hood Note,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Tears of Borgia will be mine\N{\c&H6B60A5&}Red Hood
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:07.36,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,and no one knew what he looked \Nlike beneath his hood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.97,0:17:09.52,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,That's the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.52,0:17:16.94,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What happens to the Tears of Borgia?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.94,0:17:19.87,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,A maid comes up with an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.87,0:17:22.98,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,She was played by Asahina Nagisa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.87,0:17:29.58,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,He'll find it if it's hidden, so \Nit should be kept in plain sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.58,0:17:33.60,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,A fake jewel is locked \Ninside the mansion's safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.60,0:17:37.24,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,while the real one is kept \Non the maid's finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.95,0:17:45.50,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,But Red Hood's true identity is \Nactually her boyfriend, the butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.86,0:17:47.62,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A common story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.01,0:17:50.62,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,While the thief waits for \Nan opportunity to strike,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.62,0:17:55.53,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,the maid is sent to some distant \Nmountains by the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.06,0:17:57.12,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.31,0:18:00.17,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.55,0:18:03.37,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,About your meeting with Asahina-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.37,0:18:04.27,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.56,0:18:09.37,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but Asahina-san isn't doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.37,0:18:11.71,DCMain,ATTENDANT,0000,0000,0000,,Could you come back another day?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.27,0:18:18.91,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,They're worried her symptoms might get worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:22.55,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,When you put it that way, \Nwe don't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.55,0:18:23.71,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.71,0:18:24.83,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.11,0:18:27.08,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,You're Saeki Yuri-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.08,0:18:30.08,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri was my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.08,0:18:32.89,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,What a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.89,0:18:36.84,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm first-rate Western \Nhistory professor Senju.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.15,0:18:38.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You can't say that yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.35,0:18:40.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Senju?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.91,0:18:42.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't he on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.81,0:18:47.03,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. He must know \Nabout your grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.94,0:18:52.48,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You were exactly my type.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.25,0:18:53.64,Senju,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(212,383)}Senju Hideo (88)\NWestern History Scholar
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.48,0:18:54.78,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm delighted to see you again, Yuri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.47,0:18:58.11,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,That's my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.58,0:19:05.15,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,You were the only saving grace of \Nthat incredibly unpleasant program.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.15,0:19:08.87,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,You truly were my ideal woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.15,0:19:10.79,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.79,0:19:13.17,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be shy, Yuri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.30,0:19:22.01,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we get going, Sumire-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.01,0:19:25.81,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, how rude! Don't you agree, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.08,0:19:26.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.19,0:19:31.29,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember, Yuri-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.29,0:19:34.32,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,What did Yamato TV say about that program?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.63,0:19:36.44,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.44,0:19:39.62,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! I told you \Nbecause you didn't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.62,0:19:42.64,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,The Tears of Borgia was fake!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.64,0:19:45.33,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,It never actually existed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.68,0:19:50.58,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,But Yamato TV didn't care about the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.58,0:19:53.87,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,They asked me to say it was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.87,0:19:56.46,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,A sponsor's request?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.46,0:19:58.46,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,What do they think history is?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.78,0:20:03.72,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say on the broadcast?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:07.66,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,That I'd overlook it since it was a legend,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.66,0:20:12.23,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,but that the owners embarrass themselves \Nif they insisted it was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.23,0:20:13.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.73,0:20:19.13,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,The TV station was displeased no matter \Nhow much I denied its existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.13,0:20:21.81,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one who \Nlistened to me, Yuri-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.28,0:20:24.99,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I fell in love with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.99,0:20:25.99,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.99,0:20:26.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.44,0:20:28.66,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.00,0:20:35.49,Nonogaki Real Estate,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Nonogaki Real Estate
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.67,0:20:40.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.79,0:20:43.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa-kun, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.31,0:20:45.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! Shut up, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.37,0:20:49.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa-kun! Hey, Mizusawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.01,0:20:52.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you want to talk to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.96,0:20:55.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Open up. Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.93,0:20:58.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.28,0:21:02.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mizusawa-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.76,0:21:05.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say something \Nabout the whatever of Borgia?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.18,0:21:07.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.61,0:21:12.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Something's burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.06,0:21:20.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:21.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's Mizusawa's phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.92,0:21:26.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A fire? Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.37,0:21:28.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.26,0:21:29.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hot, hot, hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.75,0:21:33.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hot, hot, hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.11,0:21:34.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.11,0:21:36.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.86,0:21:45.11,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,I warned the Asahina family that employed \Nyou not to embarrass themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.11,0:21:48.24,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,Don't put this counterfeit on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.63,0:21:52.49,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,You looked at me with your \Ncute round eyes and nodded.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.84,0:21:55.00,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,My heart was pounding.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.09,0:21:57.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.93,0:21:59.71,DCMain,SENJU,0000,0000,0000,,Boorish machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.71,0:22:01.67,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Inspector Megure?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:03.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.35,0:22:06.68,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? My father's caught in a fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.06,0:22:09.30,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,How is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.72,0:22:11.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is he all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.04,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HE6DDD5&}Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.99,0:23:49.95,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,So where are we headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.44,0:23:52.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The dam.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.20,0:23:54.95,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to \Ncheck at the filming location.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.97,0:24:00.15,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.15,0:24:01.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.37,0:24:01.96,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.96,0:24:03.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.77,0:24:06.67,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Knew what? H-Hey, Shinichi!
